      "options": {
        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "### Manage demo Blackbox targets\n\n> Tip: use a unique `DEMO_PROJECT` for interviews to avoid collisions (and use the same `DEMO_PROJECT` you started the demo with).  \n> Run these commands from the repo root (or use an absolute path to `Makefile.demo`).\n\n```bash\nexport DEMO_PROJECT=\"mon-demo\"\nexport JOB=\"blackbox-http\"\nexport TARGET=\"https://example.org\"\n\n# list current targets for the job\nmake -f stacks/monitoring/Makefile.demo ls-targets-demo \\\n  JOB=\"$JOB\" DEMO_PROJECT=\"$DEMO_PROJECT\"\n\n# add a target\nmake -f stacks/monitoring/Makefile.demo add-target-demo \\\n  JOB=\"$JOB\" TARGET=\"$TARGET\" DEMO_PROJECT=\"$DEMO_PROJECT\"\n\n# apply changes (reload Prometheus demo)\nmake -f stacks/monitoring/Makefile.demo demo-reload-prom \\\n  DEMO_PROJECT=\"$DEMO_PROJECT\" ENVFILE=\"stacks/monitoring/.env.demo\"\n\n# verify in Grafana: \"Last Reload - Prometheus\" updates and the target appears after the next scrape\n\n# remove the target\nmake -f stacks/monitoring/Makefile.demo rm-target-demo \\\n  JOB=\"$JOB\" TARGET=\"$TARGET\" DEMO_PROJECT=\"$DEMO_PROJECT\"\n\n# apply removal (reload again)\nmake -f stacks/monitoring/Makefile.demo demo-reload-prom \\\n  DEMO_PROJECT=\"$DEMO_PROJECT\" ENVFILE=\"stacks/monitoring/.env.demo\"\n\n# verify in Grafana: \"Last Reload - Prometheus\" updates and the target disappears after the next scrape\n```\n\n> Note: `ENVFILE` is only used by `demo-reload-prom` in this runbook.  \n> If your env file is not `stacks/monitoring/.env.demo`, replace the `ENVFILE=...` value accordingly.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
